[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bollywood's Bachchan and Ranaut win national film awards

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Veteran Bollywood actor Amitabh Bachchan and actress Kangana Ranaut have won the highest honours at India's prestigious national film awards.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Bachchan won best actor for his role in Piku, and Ranaut was best actress for Tanu Weds Manu Returns.
The best film award went to revenge drama Bahubali and Sanjay Leela Bhansali won best director for his movie Bajirao Mastani.
The awards are given every year by the Indian government.
This is Bachchan's fourth national film award. He won the best actor award in 1990, 2005 and 2009.
Ranaut's win marks the second consecutive time she has been given the best actress award.
The government also honours regional Indian cinema and film technicians through the annual awards.
